        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>This is a full-polarization project for continuum observations at 1.3 mm (Band 6). Default correlator set-up is chosen by the OT.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_CORRELATOR</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>Our primary goal is to resolve the magnetic field orientation on the 0.015 pc scale (corresponding to 1.1" for a source distance of 2.9 kpc), thus an angular resolution of 0.3" is needed. Our existing SMA polarization observations have a beam size of 3.4" x 2.0". To effectively recover the emission with an SMA beam, we request the largest angular scale to be 3".</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_ANGULAR_RESOLUTION</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>We aim to detect linearly polarized dust continuum emission at 1.3 mm (Band 6) with an angular resolution of 0.3". Toward the target position, our existing SMA polarization observations have revealed a flux of 20 mJy at 0.88 mm within a 3.4" x 2.0" beam, with a polarization degree of 1%. We expect a similar polarization degree for the proposed ALMA observations at 1.3 mm. Considering the beam size and frequency differences between the SMA and ALMA observations, we expect a flux of 0.067 mJy within an ALMA synthesized beam, which is calculated by 20*(0.3^2/3.4/2.0)*(0.88/1.3)^3.5, where we assume a smooth distribution of the polarized emission within the SMA synthesized beam and adopt a typical dust opacity index of 1.5. We therefore request an RMS of 0.013 mJy/beam, to achieve a signal-to-noise ratio (S/N) of 5.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_SENSITIVITY</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
    </prj:ScienceGoal>
